Definition: habitual intoxication
Example: prolonged and excessive intake of alcoholic drinks leading to a breakdown in health and an addiction to alcohol such that abrupt deprivation leads to severe withdrawal symptoms
Synonyms: alcohol_addiction, inebriation, verb, consumption, inebriate, drunkenness, drug_addiction, habitual, intoxication, prolonged, and, excessive, intake, of, alcoholic, drinks, leading, to, a, breakdown, in, health, an, addiction, alcohol, such, that, abrupt, deprivation, leads, severe, withdrawal, symptoms
Category: noun.state
